Ambiguity in numeric variables
================
Deepayan Sarkar

\[NOTE: This requires a specific branch of nhanesA, and may not work
with trunk until the relevant changes are merged\]

``` r
## mpub <- nhanesManifest("public", sizes = FALSE)
## tables <- mpub$Table
tables <- nhanesA:::.nhanesQuery("select TableName from Metadata.QuestionnaireDescriptions")
tables <- tables$TableName
```

Go through all tables in the manifest and check for ambiguities, as
reported by `nhanesA:::checkAmbiguous()`.

``` r
for (t in tables) {
    status <- try(nhanesA:::checkAmbiguous(t), silent = TRUE)
    if (inherits(status, "try-error")) {
        cat("-----Table:", t, "----------\n")
        cat("ERROR: ", as.character(status))
    }
    if (!is.null(status)) {
        cat("-----Table:", t, "----------\n")
        print(status)
    }
}
```
